quran[24]{c,v,t,f}:
  56,91,"Then [the angels will say], "
  56,92,"But if he was of the deniers [who were] astray,"
  56,93,"Then [for him is] accommodation of scalding water"
  68,25,"And they went early in determination, [assuming themselves] able.{1}",footnotes:1:[To carry out their plan, confident of their ability.]
  68,26,"But when they saw it, they said, "
  68,27,"Rather, we have been deprived."
  69,22,"In an elevated garden,"
  69,23,"Its [fruit] to be picked hanging near."
  69,24,"[They will be told], ",footnotes:1:[Literally, "advanced" in anticipation of reward in the Hereafter.]
  70,16,"A remover of exteriors.{1}",footnotes:1:[This refers to the skin of the head or of the body or to the body extremities - which will be burned away.]
  70,17,"It invites he who turned his back [on truth] and went away [from obedience]"
  70,18,"And collected [wealth] and hoarded."
  71,13,"What is [the matter] with you that you do not attribute to Allāh [due] grandeur"
  71,14,"While He has created you in stages?{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., in various progressive states and conditions.  See also 22:5 and 23:12-14 in reference to development of the embryo.]
  71,15,"Do you not consider how Allāh has created seven heavens in layers{1}",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 67:3.]
  72,10,"And we do not know [therefore] whether evil is intended for those on earth or whether their Lord intends for them a right course."
  72,11,"And among us are the righteous, and among us are [others] not so; we were [of] divided ways.{1}",footnotes:1:[In opinion, belief and religious practice.]
  72,12,"And we have become certain that we will never cause failure to Allāh upon earth, nor can we escape Him by flight."
  73,4,"Or add to it, and recite the Qur’ān with measured recitation."
  73,5,"Indeed, We will cast upon you a heavy word.{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., the revelation, which when descending on the Prophet (ﷺ) bore down upon him with a great weight.  Another meaning is "important ordinances."]
  73,6,"Indeed, the hours of the night are more effective for concurrence [of heart and tongue]{1} and more suitable for words.{2}",footnotes:1:[Another accepted interpretation of the same words is \"Indeed, arising at night is more difficult...,\" meaning that it will only be done by sincere believers and not others.],footnotes:2:[i.e., for recitation of the Qur’ān and for hearing and understanding it.]
  74,1,"O you who covers himself [with a garment],{1}",footnotes:1:[Referring to the Prophet (ﷺ).]
  74,2,"Arise and warn."
  74,3,"And your Lord glorify."
